==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|vilificare|vīlificāre|lang=la}}, present active infinitive of {{term|vilifico|vīlificō|villify|lang=la}}, 

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈvɪl.ɪ.faɪ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-vilify.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|vilif|i|ed}}

# {{transitive}} To say [[defamatory]] things about someone or something.
# {{transitive}} To [[belittle]] through speech; to [[put down]].

